The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | StanChart chooses Bindra for plum post
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      StanChart chooses Bindra for plum post
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                           Bindra: New role                                  
	Mumbai, Dec. 11: Standard Chartered today appointed Jaspal Bindra as group executive director.         
	Bindra follows other high ranking Indians such as Citis Indian-American chief executive Vikram Pandit and StanCharts former CEO Rana Talwar to a senior position in a multinational bank         
	His appointment, effective January 1, is part of a series of senior-level changes made by the London-based bank to enhance the experience, depth and diversity of its board and strengthen governance.         
	Standard Chartered said Bindra would continue to oversee its Asian operations. He is currently the chief executive officer for the Asian region.        
	Bindra joined Standard Chartered in 1998. He is a director of the bank and has held his current position since 2007. He has key international experiences, including previous roles as the global head of client relationships and chief executive officer of StanChart India.         
	As the CEO for the Asian region, Bindras responsibilities include developing strategy, driving stronger regulatory and government relations, addressing governance issues and monitoring performance. He oversees all M amp;A activities in Asia and acts as a senior contact role for major clients, regulators, and governments.         
	Previously he was the regional CEO, South East and South Asia, from December 2005 to September 2007.         
	Before joining Standard Chartered Bank, Bindra was with UBS Investment Banking. He began his career with Bank of America in 1984 and worked across treasury markets and consumer banking in India and Singapore.                                                                                                                                       
